cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes historical networks of world leaders, which can be seen as a social network. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses cultural anthropology and the differences in historical worldview between Western and Eastern cultures. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses Wikipedia as a data source and may discuss the technical aspects of data collection and analysis. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper may discuss the user interface and user experience of the Wikipedia platform. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper may use natural language processing techniques to analyze the text in the Wikipedia articles.
